HARDWARE: CPU Input & Output

The movies states that all input, store, process and output information. Some examples 
keyboard, mouse, video, microphone all input information.
The CPU then processes the info and converts it to binaryand then into memory.
Output can be a monitor, a sound a video, and robotic arm, or a cutting device.
With a self check out the input is the item scanned. The PLU. The CPU is the cash register
or UScan machine. The output is the cost displayed. You then input your credit card info which
is scanned into the CPU again your info deduted from your card and the item paid for all done in binary
and then output is the receipt.
